A truly impressive trophy, this stuffed bear must measure a solid eight feet in length, leaving you to wonder what mighty hunter managed to take the magnificent creature down.

Value.value: Whoever stuffed the bear did a magnificent job in covering up the cause of this prime ursal specimen’s demise.

Though the wound cannot be seen on the treated pelt, you’ve heard all manner of wild stories from the various bar patrons as to how the mighty beast was killed, many claiming to have done the deed themselves of course. One common thread between stories; the bear was killed somewhere deep in the Timberlands, north of the region most townsfolk harvest lumber from.

Piecing together local rumor from the bar patrons and others in town, three possibilities present themselves. One claims that Gustav felled the beast himself with only his timber axe, when Guldorand was first founded. Another claims that the first ranger to protect the area, Araegis, felled the beast with a single arrow and gifted it to Guldorand as a symbol of his protection. The last, claims that the bear is not dead at all, petrified by a powerful sorceress named Annabel who lives in a cabin outside of town. All stories agree that the bear came from north of the Timberlands.
Nothin' but trouble in the trees, ye ask me. Things rustlin' and watchin' in the brush that got no business bein' there...
Jacho's a good lad, done good by this town. Anythin' ye can help him with'll earn ye our gratitude, an' maybe even a free pint.
If we can just keep those damn mines clear, we might be able to expand our commerce. It would be nice if we didn't have to rely solely on timber for the town's success.

We've been doing alright for ourselves since rebuilding the town. Seems like Amia is finally starting to realize how big a part we play in the economic stability of the region. And that we aren't just a bunch of backwater rubes.
Feels good to be out on the hills again, doing an honest day's work. I don't agree with everything Cordor did, but the Commonwealth got us back on our feet.

That barmy gnome in town spends far too much time tinkering and not enough earning a keep in the world ... but I suppose he's not hurting anyone, unlike that relative he talks about higher in the mountain.
Jacho's an old friend of mine, I'm only here because of him. He's asked me to come to town now and then and help teach the children about the wilderness around Guldorand.
Most of my time I scout higher in the Skull Crags. I keep telling the guard here they should keep a closer eye on the Crystal Spire area. We'll see if they listen.

value.0: "Damn I look good in my black pants.."

Value.value: The folks in town here helped drag me back from a very dark place... they gave me a job as the barkeep for the new Logjammer... I can't begin to thank them enough.
We don't stand on formalities, just tap what you'd like to drink and leave your coin on the bar, we're all friends here.
